casebody.data:
Lorenzo D. WASHINGTON, Appellant,
v.
STATE of Missouri, Respondent. WD 81354 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: April 30, 2019 Susan L. Hogan, Kansas City, MO, for appellant. Justin Moody, Jefferson City, MO, for respondent. Before Division Two: Thomas N. Chapman, Presiding Judge, Mark D. Pfeiffer, Judge and Cynthia L. Martin, Judge

ORDER

Per curiam:

Lorenzo D. Washington ("Washington") appeals from the motion court's denial of his Rule 24.035 motion for post-conviction relief which alleged ineffective assistance of counsel in failing to provide Washington with sufficient information to knowingly, intelligently, and voluntarily enter into a guilty plea. Finding no error, we affirm. Rule 84.16(b).
